The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, Dec. 20 (PTI): An old age home resident in New Delhi was burnt to death in his bed early this morning after an electrician allegedly set the dormitory on fire and locked it from outside.          
	Suresh Kumar, who hails from Kerala, claimed that he did it to draw media attention to his ordeals, additional commissioner of police K.C. Dwivedi said. He has been arrested.                  
	New Delhi (PTI): Police have saved an 11-day-old girl and an eight-year-old boy from four people who were allegedly running an adoption racket. Dr Atul Sharma and three others have been arrested for buying children from all over the country and selling them to childless couples, a senior official said .                   
	New Delhi (PTI): A man has been sentenced to life for killing a male friend who resisted his sexual advances three years ago. Rehman had smashed a soft drink bottle on his friend Tarikuls head, fatally injuring him in their house in February 2007, the prosecution said.                  
	 Lucknow (PTI) A 27-year-old software engineer became friendly with a young woman on the internet, distorted her photographs, and threatened to circulate the pictures unless she paid him Rs 30,000. A joint police team has arrested Shoaib Khan, who confessed to the blackmail.                   
	Ludhiana (PTI) A 35-year-old man has died after setting himself on fire in front of a deputy police commissioners office. Police said they had recovered a suicide note saying: Had there been any law in the country this decision would have been different. The note did not elaborate further.                   
	Cuddalore (PTI): A mini-bus carrying 32 workers rammed into a school van at Semamkuppam village in Tamil Nadu, killing four students and injuring 34 people. Police said the bus driver had lost control of the vehicle while trying to avoid an elderly man.
                                                                                                                                              
